@startuml AC-02_Forged_Payment_Webhook

title AC-02 — Forged Payment Confirmation Webhook via HMAC Bypass\nSTRIDE: Spoofing | Severity: Critical | Mitigation: M-02

left to right direction

skinparam usecase {
  BackgroundColor<< abuse >> #FFCCCC
  BorderColor<< abuse >> #CC0000
  FontColor<< abuse >> #CC0000
  BackgroundColor<< normal >> #DDEEFF
  BorderColor<< normal >> #336699
  BackgroundColor<< impact >> #FFF3CD
  BorderColor<< impact >> #856404
}
skinparam actorBackgroundColor #EEF
skinparam actorBorderColor #336699
skinparam noteFontSize 10

actor "Payment Gateway\n(Legitimate)" as gateway #DDEEFF
actor "External Attacker" as attacker #FFCCCC

rectangle "VendNet System" {
  usecase "Receive Legitimate\nPayment Confirmation (EP3)" as UC2 << normal >>
  usecase "Recover HMAC-SHA256\nSecret (brute-force / leak)" as AC2a << abuse >>
  usecase "Forge Payment Webhook\nwith Crafted HMAC Signature" as AC2 << abuse >>
  usecase "Trigger Fraudulent\nProduct Dispensing" as AC2b << abuse >>
}

gateway --> UC2

attacker --> AC2a
attacker --> AC2
AC2a ..> AC2  : <<enables>>
AC2 ..> UC2   : <<threatens>>
AC2 ..> AC2b  : <<extends>>

note right of AC2a
  **Preconditions:**
  • Callback URL (EP3) reachable from internet
  • HMAC secret weak / leaked in Git history
  • No mutual TLS on EP3 inbound channel
  • No cross-validation with Gateway ledger
end note

note right of AC2b
  **Impact:**
  Integrity: fraudulent Sale records with
  PaymentStatus.COMPLETED
  Financial: free product dispensing at scale,
  inventory depletion without revenue
  Business: contractual breach with
  Payment Gateway
end note

note bottom of attacker
  **Attack vector:**
  {"transactionRef":"TXN-FAKE-001","status":"COMPLETED",
   "amount":2.50,"machineId":"M-07","productId":"P-42"}
  + X-Signature: sha256=<computed_hmac>
end note

@enduml
